  "prompt": "Don't know what happen to my friend (girl) stopped messaging to me or talk to me..no reason what to do?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Initial Check\n- Send a calm, friendly message asking if everything is okay\n- Don't sound accusatory or angry\n- Give them space and time to respond\n\n2. Possible Ways to Reach Out\n- Text message\n- Social media message\n- Email\n- Phone call (if appropriate)\n\n3. Potential Reasons for Silence\n- Personal issues\n- Misunderstanding\n- Busy schedule\n- Relationship changes\n- Personal stress\n\n4. What NOT to Do\n- Don't spam messages\n- Avoid angry or desperate texts\n- Don't jump to negative conclusions\n- Don't badger or pressure them\n\n5. If No Response\n- Respect their space\n- Focus on yourself\n- Continue with your own life\n- Stay open but don't obsess\n\n6. If Concerned\n- Ask mutual friends if everything is okay\n- Consider if there might be a serious issue\n- Be supportive, not demanding\n\n7. Long-term\n- Reflect on your friendship/relationship\n- Learn from the experience\n- Be patient and understanding\n\nRemember, communication is a two-way process, and people have different communication styles and personal boundaries.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
